items.name: Dooli
items.description:
About model

I created this model together with my friend Alice, who is an excellent photographer and has an unrealistically cool sense of beauty and aesthetics. Together we selected the best of her works and trained this LoRA so that each of you could repeat this incredible style!

You can watch her work on the Aistethic telegram channel, as well as on the 500px resource.

How to use

It is recommended to write the following tokens: flower, ice, vegetation, mashrooms, dimmed, lowkey, vignette, dark, glow, water, detailed.

Copy the prompt and parameters from the preview to this model — you will not lose.

Which model works best with

It is best to use the Deliberate_v2 model, but you can combine this LoRA with other solutions focused on photorealism, model will work perfectly with them.

Links and resources

Alisa's Telegram channel.
You will find help in my telegram chat.
My Telegram channel.

items.name: [Guide] Read Invisible Prompt On Civitai
items.description:
Read Invisible Prompt On Civitai

Before 2 months ago,i reported this bug to civitai

https://civitai.com/questions/349/why-cant-the-prompt-automatically-read-uploaded-images-now

but they dont keep more attention on it.

So i made this guide for Read Invisible Prompt On Civitai

1、Open your browser, such as Chrome, Firefox, Safari or Edge.

I use Chrome for example.

2、Go to the official website of the user script manager, such as Tampermonkey or Greasemonkey.

I installed Tampermonkey

3、Open this script and install it.

https://greasyfork.org/scripts/459579-stable-diffusion-image-metadata-viewer

4、Find a image on civitai,even it cant show any meta data.

For instance, I'll use the first cover of this model as an example.

5、Right click image and choose open with new tab

also you can choose copy the image address and open the new tab to browse it.

https://image.civitai.com/xG1nkqKTMzGDvpLrqFT7WA/8af758cc-37c2-48ca-aa41-4729db53eec0/width=1840/grid-0001-1.jpeg

5.5 this BUG is fixed,dont need new extension for chrome.

Please update to version 0.24 over~

5. 5、If you cant see button in this example, it seems that latest browser Content-Security-Policy blocked script.

this is a BUG for script with lastest browser, wait to fix or use this extension to close CSP in png page.

https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/disable-content-security/ieelmcmcagommplceebfedjlakkhpden

Install this↑ and click extension button then background will be black and script button will show.

6、Left-click the button in the top left corner, and prompt you want to know will be displayed.

7、if you cant find button, it seems that this image dont have extra prompt.

items.name: Lysergic
items.description:
If you appreciate what I’m doing feel free to https://www.buymeacoffee.com/Uzia or share some of your generations! I love to see them.

(On that note though, imagery depicting sexual violence/abuse will be reported immediately.)

Lysergic. This model is the lightest of heart among the trinity. It’s cartoonyer style shrugs off a lot of the darker aspects of its siblings and instead brings a more vibrant and dynamic style to the table.

All preview images are done without embeddings and with Hires. fix: upscale 2.  Steps 20. Denoising 0.5.  Latent.  All are cherry picked from batches of three.

All images are made in A1111. Many of the prompts are the same as my other model to give a feeling of the differences, and similarities, between each. Due to time constraints I won’t be uploading previews from InvokeAi.

modelVersions.name: Lysergic.v2.0

Ingredients: Lysergic.v1 - mistoonAmethyst - icomix_v03 - Opiate.v.1 Huge thanks to the creators of those checkpoints!!! - (Accept myself, or maybe myself too, thanks past me) - I feel like their work has helped me hit on something beautiful. It was certainly a pleasure to explore V.2's capabilities, and I really hope you guys enjoy it as much as I have.

Improvements: Everything I think... Maybe not hands, but that is a fight for later.

All preview images are done without embeddings and with Hires. fix: upscale 2.  Steps 20. Denoising 0.5.  Latent.  All are cherry picked from batches of three.

What else can I say: Enjoy the Trip.

items.name: Feet Not the Primary Subject of the Photo
items.description:
Not satisfied with current state of feet models on Stable Diffusion, I set out to train one based on content available that has feet in the frame(s), but not as the primary focus on the photo. This model helps with more photorealistic details on feet and often emphasizes particular positions that are probably well known by foot fetish lovers. Captioned with BLIP.

On its own, it sometimes will impose a stylistic look (gold, vintage pinup type of feel), but merges excellently with other models. Mixing with chillout, Realistic Vision have given me lots of fun results. Still loads of training and input data work I could do so this is just the start.

Made some good content with it? Why not post them? :)

items.name: Kasia
items.description:
If you like my contributions to the community, please consider Buying Me A Coffee or check out my other sites on AllMyLinks

TRAINING INFO

  • Trained on 170 photos (face & full body)

  • Trained at 768 resolution, so 768x768 inpainting works great

  • "Dormroom" is also trained into the LoRA, so adding it to your prompts should give a good result

RECOMMENDED SETTINGS

Prompts: For a full list of the prompts/captioned used for training, check the Lora file's metadata in your webgui

txt2img: A weight of 0.7-0.9 will give the best mix of likeness and flexibility.

Inpainting: A weight of 0.75-85 will give the best low-noise likeness. If you want the absolute best likeness, switch your checkpoint to SD15 since that's the model on which it was trained.

Face restoration: isn't usually necessary, but I recommend setting your face restoration strength inside auto1111 settings to something like 0.7-0.8 which makes the effect less than the default setting of 0.5.

GETTING THE BEST LIKENESS WITH LORA'S

The checkpoint you use can heavily influence the likeness of a celebrity Lora. I train my Lora's on SD15, so you'll get the best likeness on any model that used SD15 as the base model. See this example for how a checkpoint can influence the look of a Lora.

Monifa Jansen is a Curaçaoan model and social media personality.

1500-step TI trained on a dataset of 18 images with my usual settings.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

How to create a good prompt using my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of (m0nifa:0.99), a woman, RAW, close portrait photo, long brown coat, ((turtleneck sweater:1.2), trousers, long haircut, slim body, (high detailed skin:1.2), 8k uhd, dslr, soft lighting, high quality, film grain, Fujifilm XT3 sharp focus, f 5.6"

items.name: Haste - Epic Seven
items.description:
Guidelines for better generations:
• Recommended weight: 0.7 to 0.9
• If the blood vial in his choker is not looking right, add "red collar" to the prompt. That should solve the problem.
• You can prompt chewing gum if you want his classic bubble gum.
• For some reason, sometimes the model will hyperfixate on his legs/shoes. Taking the word boots out of the prompt solves that problem.
• You should probably be able to make him wear clothes that are not his main costume, just... getting him to take his jacket off might be a bit difficult. I'll fix that in a future version.

LoRA for the best vampire boy from e7! Hooray!

It was difficult to source the material for this, I had to do it manually and tag it by hand, and it's also my first lora, so I was a bit scared while doing it, but I'm fairly satisfied with the result.
I will come back to it one of these days to improve some stuff, and fix a few things (Let's just say Haste really likes his jacket here. Pretty clingy with it. Very difficult to convince him to take it off.)

That said, I hope you like it!

Ps.:

His tattoo is a bit all over the place. Since there is no image in the world that depicts how the tattoo looks like under his clothing, the lora just figures where it should probably be and slaps it there. Sometimes it covers the wrong leg (or both legs) with it. I don't really mind it, though.

items.name: RoseRendered
items.description:
V2.0 Released: A pretty big upgrade from 1.1, primarily achieved by mixing in the excellent Brixel Core at 30%. It adds a massive amount of flexibility to the model, letting it do a variety of lineart styles, and even fun chibis, while retaining the soul and core of the style. This also tamps what peculiarities in prompting were present, and makes it a touch more responsive to many things.

RoseRendered is focused mainly on achieving expressive characters in a western, somewhat rendered style. Previously it was a counterpart to my Drawn Mix, but recent developments mean it can do most things that model can do, with a bunch of other improvements and added capability.

The original form of this model was trained off of Hassaku(NSFW), though it's diverged very significantly over the course of multiple sessions of training. As well as my additions, some of Brixel Core has been added to greatly improve the range of styles it is able to achieve.

Tips for use:

  • I recommend using 40+ steps, at least with Euler A. You can get away with fewer, but it leads to more inpainting

  • I use FastNegativeEmbedding, which includes a hand improvement. If you don't use this, or even if you do, a negative embedding such as one of the badhand embeddings can improve hands

  • "detailed face" is recommended for non anime face styles.

  • Trained with primarily booru tags. If you're having trouble getting a result, figuring out what it would be on danbooru may help.

Image workflow and settings for examples: (Most of the initial gallery of examples are no longer inpainted, as I've improved my GPU and no longer have to generate at quite as low resolution.

  • Euler A generating at (usually) 512x512 with 36 steps at CLIP SKIP 2

  • Upscaled 1.5x using the 4x-UltraSharp and Hires. fix

  • Quickly inpainting faces that required it using the method above, and in a couple cases a second pass to fix a wonky eye or small detail

  • No inpainting of hands or held objects was performed.

Nerdy stuff you may or may not need to know:

  • WD-VAE-v1 is baked in, inherited from Hassaku. I may experiment and upload a version without a VAE.

  • Trained at CLIP SKIP 2

items.name: sh4g0d
items.description:
Hi!


"Presenting "sh4g0d". This LORA uses a different approach than the previous one but turned out really good (I think).

This LORA will bias your generations towards a cybernetic/horned style. Works very well for animals mixing (with some "advanced prompting"), works very good for simple portraiture prompts and even it works at 1 with some degree of variations, it shines at values 0.6-0.8.

Not recommended for objects or isolated gadgets but works fine with the right prompts. I made some crystal jar, glasses, beds, cars, etc. But the intention is more for characters.

Best usage is:
- Not using "sh4g0d" keyword at first (the LORA is very strong but without being overfitted) and you can decide if use sh4g0d (previously was another unreleased LORA that acted as "mechanizer", that's why it acts this way) or not to power your costume/char, etc.

IMPORTANT!

I wrote an article here and it's like my finetunning diary for the ones interested with releases upcoming, trainings done, exclusive patreon models previews, personal thoughts, etc. So if you want to see what I'm planning or what I'm into, feel free to take a look.

If you enjoy these LORA please check our exclusive content in Patreon where we train more styles like this one and some more complex, custom and experimental things:
https://www.patreon.com/user?u=90661954

Thanks a lot for your support and go crazy with this thing!

This model is based on anything4.5 trained from the picture of Hyouuma, and it is recommended to use weights between 0.6 and 0.8.

There have been many controversies about the training and use of art style models, but they are also a difficult part to avoid in the process of AI painting progress.

Therefore, it is recommended to use such art style models as a kind of existence similar to potions, by matching Loras of different art styles with different weights to form images with different styles (although this may lead to bad results, it is worth trying).Alternatively, it can be used to match your favorite character models. Anyway, I hope not to compare it with the artist's own work and make rude remarks, which will harm the community's environment.

At the same time, there are still many problems to be discovered in this model. In short, hope you have a good time.
